    <h1 style="text-align:center;">HTML Reference Page</h1>
    <h3>HTML</h3>
    <p>The tag for HTML is < html > It defines the root of an HTML document</p>
    <h3>Header</h3>
    <p>< head >	A container for all the head elements such as title, scripts, styles, meta information, and more</p>
    <h3>Title</h3>
    <p> < title > </p>
    <h3>Body</h3>
    <p>< body >	Defines the document's body</p>
    <h3>Headings</h3>
    <p>< h1 > to < h6 >	Defines HTML headings. Depending on the number it is given on its relevence is what depends the size of the header. < h1 > would be the largest header and < h6 > would be the smallest header.</p>
    <h3>Paragraphs</h3>
    <p>To make a paragraph in HTML you need to use < p > < / p > </p>
    <p>An example of how to use it would be < p >This is a paragraph.< / p >
    < p >This is another paragraph.< / p ></p>
    
    <h3>Breaks</h3>
    <p> < br > </p>
    <h3>Lines</h3>
    <p> < hr > </p>
    <h3>Comments</h3>
    <p>To write comments you would need to use this < !-- Write your comments here -- > 
    You could also write it like this < !-- This is a comment -- >
< p >This is a paragraph.< /p >
< !-- Remember to add more information here -- >
</p>
    <h3>Links</h3>
    <p>An example of a url is < a href="Your site here">Your message here< /a >
</p>
    <h3>Images</h3>
    <p> < img > </p>
    <h3>Lists</h3>
    <p> < ul >< ol > < li > </p>
    <h3>Tables</h3>
    <p> < table > < tr > < th > < td > </p>
    <h3>Blocks</h3>
    <p> < div > </p>
  </body>
